%I A397076 #6 Jun 24 2026 21:49:53
%S A397076 1,2,9,184,585803
%N A397076 Number of NPN-equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n variables whose deterministic decision-tree complexity D(f) is equal to n.
%C A397076 The deterministic decision-tree complexity (deterministic query complexity) D(f) of a Boolean function f is the minimum, over all decision trees computing f, of the tree depth (the worst-case number of input bits queried). We count the NPN-equivalence classes (functions up to negation of input variables, permutation of input variables, and negation of the output) of n-variable Boolean functions with full decision-tree complexity, D(f) = n.
%C A397076 a(5) = 585803 was obtained from a complete census of all 616126 NPN classes of Boolean functions on at most 5 variables.
%Y A397076 Cf. A000370 (number of NPN-equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n or fewer variables), A397074 (sensitivity), A397075 (degree).
%K A397076 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A397076 1,2
